step4:xml views

we actually created what call SAP/M/ext control inside the index.js. So, and
this worked, but imagine if we had um if I open the index.js, we go to our web
index.js, JS we created this text control and imagine if we have about 50
controls inside the same file. This will be a chaotic mess and so SAP UI5 is
built using what we call model view controller and that is what we are going
to be doing today. So the model view controller is actually an architecture which the abbreviation is MVC and the M
stand for model the V stand for view and the C for controller. So this means that when you have a view this describes what
the UI that's the user interface will look like and the controller contains the logic the business logic while the
model contains the data. So we're going to look at all this. Now we will then move our UI code that is for example the
one we created the text control from JavaScript into a dedicated XML view. So we're going to be creating view now and this will make our code to be cleaner,
more readable and easier to maintain. So think of this so think of this like building a proper user interface
structure. So instead of having the controls in one JavaScript file, we are going to create the XML view. 